### EdTech Sheet-Integrator API — manual smoke test
### Open in VS Code (REST Client extension) or Rider HTTP Client.
### Variables flow top-to-bottom: run requests in order.

@host = http://localhost:5000

### 1. Liveness — should return 200 with no body
GET {{host}}/health/live

### 2. Readiness — depends on SQL Server reachability
GET {{host}}/health/ready

### 3. Mint a dev Instructor JWT (Development env only)
# @name devToken
POST {{host}}/dev/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "gabe@local"
}

### Capture token from previous response
@token = {{devToken.response.body.token}}

### 4. Create an assessment (requires Instructor token)
# @name createdAssessment
POST {{host}}/api/v1/assessments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Geography & math quiz",
  "questions": [
    {
      "questionId": "Q1",
      "prompt": "Capital of France?",
      "correctAnswer": "Paris",
      "points": 1,
      "matchMode": "exact",
      "numericTolerance": null
    },
    {
      "questionId": "Q2",
      "prompt": "Pi to two decimals?",
      "correctAnswer": "3.14",
      "points": 5,
      "matchMode": "numeric",
      "numericTolerance": 0.01
    }
  ]
}

@assessmentId = {{createdAssessment.response.body.id}}

### 5. Read the assessment back (open endpoint)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/{{assessmentId}}

### 6. Upload a CSV submission and grade it
###    Save the body below as alice.csv first, then this request streams it.
###    CSV body (header + 2 rows):
###       QuestionId,Response
###       Q1,Paris
###       Q2,3.14
# @name gradedSubmission
POST {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/{{assessmentId}}/submissions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----test-boundary

------test-boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="studentIdentifier"

alice@example.com
------test-boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="alice.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

QuestionId,Response
Q1,Paris
Q2,3.14
------test-boundary--

@submissionId = {{gradedSubmission.response.body.id}}

### 7. Fetch the persisted graded submission
GET {{host}}/api/v1/submissions/{{submissionId}}

### 8. List submissions for the assessment (paged, newest first)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/{{assessmentId}}/submissions?page=1&pageSize=20

### 9. Negative path — bad token returns 401
GET {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/{{assessmentId}}
# (Open endpoint — should still succeed. The 401 negative case is the POST below.)

### 10. Negative path — missing assessment returns 404 ProblemDetails
GET {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 11. Negative path — unsupported file type returns 415
###     (.txt extension is rejected by the parser factory.)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/assessments/{{assessmentId}}/submissions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----test-boundary

------test-boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="studentIdentifier"

alice@example.com
------test-boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="alice.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

unrelated content
------test-boundary--
